    "Similarly, the GLMM including the categorical predictor (marginal Pseudo-R 2 =.05; total Pseudo-R 2 =.36) showed that the effect of type of new word was significant, with Critical Lures being falsely recognized more often than Unrelated Lures, b = 1.01, z = 3.73, p <.001.",
    "These two models had an AIC respectively of 3747 and 3763, and thus since the ΔAIC = 16, the model including the continuous predictor is 2981 times more likely to be a better model than the other foot_3 (Fig. 6C).",
    "Subsequent sensitivity analyses conducted on 1000 simulations revealed a high observed power (95% CI 95-100%) for both models.",
    "In the present study, we described FMG, the first tool that automatically creates lists for the DRM, a widely used experimental paradigm to induce and investigate memory production.",
